712056f-a.text:
West 33rd Street, north side, between Eighth and Seventh Aves. View shows empty lots utilized as a bus terminal, with an entrance on West 34th
Street.
September 24, 1931.
P. L. Sperr.
According to the New York Times of December 7, 1936 these vacant 1ots, Nos. 225 to 33, will be improved with a 1-story theatre and store building that will extend through to 234-236 West 34th Street.

712053f-b.text:
West 33rd Street, north side, west from a point to the west of Seventh Avenue, showing the rear of the Greyhound Bus Terminal and surrounding features. This transportation facility runs thru to 34th Street, in the center of the block bounded by Seventh and Eighth Avenues. Beyond the latter thoroughfare are the outstanding Printing Crafts Bldg.
and the Hotel New Yorker.
September 2, 1940
No's. 1-2-3
P. L. Sperr
